a. Learn how to create a multi-page website with Home, About, and Contact pages.
b. Learn how to add navigation links for seamless page transitions.
c. Learn how to structure content for a professional website using HTML and CSS.


Home Page (index.html)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Home - My Website</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; background-color: #f2f2f2; text-align: center; }
        nav { background: #333; padding: 10px; }
        nav a { color: white; margin: 15px; text-decoration: none; }
        nav a:hover { color: yellow; }
        .box { background: white; padding: 30px; width: 60%; margin: 40px auto; border-radius: 10px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <nav>
        <a href="index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="about.html">About</a>
        <a href="contact.html">Contact</a>
    </nav>

    <div class="box">
        <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
        <p>This is the home page of a simple multi-page website using HTML and CSS.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

